race.comment: A small field, but it's competitive. NEOCLASSICISM (8) deserved the 58 win this track and trip and will carry just 51kg this grade with a 3kg claimer aboard. That brings him right into it and with average luck he's capable of repeating the dose. LA SOEUR (5) led and won over this distance in a 70. He's back on track and will use the inside gate. Carries more weight, but the well-bred mare is a decent chance to repeat. TROPIC SANDS (3) resumed in the same race beaten 1L. He's been improved by the Robl yard and is proven second-up.  A player as well. SILVER WARRIOR (2) keeps a 3kg claim and is an on-pacer back 360m in trip. He's a hope if things go his way.
